With unique stallholders from across the Lowveld, the Steiltes Family Night Market was bustling with visitors who came to support the many local exhibitors on Friday July 1. ALSO READ: Karen Zoid rocks Mbombela at Blue Moon Held at the corner of Suiderkruis and Aurora streets at the Nelspruit Masons and Lions Community Centre, the market drew exhibitors from Mbombela, Kaapsehoop, Komatipoort, White River and beyond. The organiser Monica Arnott said, considering the cold weather on Friday, the turnout to the market was much larger than expected. “It was a fabulous evening and we even had a visitor from Cape Town who said he had enjoyed the market,” said Arnott. “The Lowveld has the most talented exhibitors. I am always blown away at how hard they work.” ALSO READ: Car boot sale held in aid of White River SPCA’s animals The market is held on the last Friday of every month. To find out more about it and its wonderful exhibitors, visit the Facebook and Instagram page at Steiltes Family Night Market. 